ESL-Bundle is the result of various long-running collaborations involving
many researchers, research groups and engineers in the fields of electronic
structure, quantum chemistry, and computer science. The following author
list is known to be incomplete. Feel free to extend it, so that it better
reflects reality.


The source code building framework of ESL-Bundle has been originally
written by:

  Damien Caliste
  Alin Marin Elena
  Micael Oliveira
  Yann Pouillon

It is distributed under the Mozilla Public License version 2.


ESL-Bundle contains a modified version of JHBuild, a package the original
source code can be found at:

  https://github.com/GNOME/jhbuild

JHBuild is part of the GNOME Project and is distributed under the GNU General
Public License version 2.


ESL-Bundle builds the following libraries:

  - Fdict and Flook, written by Nick Ruebner Papior, and distributed under
    the GNU Lesser Public General License version 3.
    https://github.com/zerothi/fdict
    https://github.com/ElectronicStructureLibrary/flook

  - Futile, written by the Developers of BigDFT, and distributed under
    the GNU General Public License version 3.
    http://bigdft.org/

  - LibFDF, written by the Developers of SIESTA, and distributed under
    the BSD 3-clause License.
    https://launchpad.net/libfdf

  - LibPSML, written by Alberto Garcia, and distributed under
    the BSD 3-clause License.
    https://launchpad.net/libpsml

  - LibXC, written by Miguel Marques and Micael Oliveira, and distributed
    under the Mozilla Public License version 2.
    https://gitlab.com/libxc/libxc

  - PSolver, written by the Developers of BigDFT, and distributed under
    the GNU General Public License version 3.
    http://bigdft.org/

  - Pspio, written by Micael Oliveira, Yann Pouillon and Matthieu Verstraete,
    and distributed under the GNU Lesser General Public License version 2.1.
    https://gitlab.e-cam2020.eu/esl/pspio

  - XMLF90, written by Alberto Garcia, Jon Wakelin, Toby White and Dan Wilson,
    and distributed under the BSD 2-clause License.

  - LibYAML, written by Kirill Simonov, and distributed under the BSD 2-clause
    License.


ESL-Bundle also includes the ELSI Bundle, which contains:

  - ELPA, written by the ELPA Consortium, and distributed under the
    the GNU Lesser Public General License version 3.
    https://gitlab.mpcdf.mpg.de/elpa/elpa

  - ELSI, written by the ELSI Team, and distributed under the BSD 3-clause
    License.
    http://elsi-interchange.org/

  - LibOMM, written by Fabiano Corsetti, and distributed under the
    BSD 2-clause License.
    https://gitlab.e-cam2020.eu/esl/omm

  - MatrixSwitch, written by Fabiano Corsetti,and distributed under the
    BSD 2-clause License (included in LibOMM).
    https://gitlab.e-cam2020.eu/esl/omm

  - PEXSI, written by Alberto Garcia, Georg Huhs, Lin Lin and Chao Yang,
    and distributed under the BSD 3-clause License.
    https://math.berkeley.edu/~linlin/pexsi/

  - SIPs, written by Murat Keceli, and distributed under the BSD 2-clause
    License.
    http://bitbucket.org/keceli/qetsc

